BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BW1LwtBOsgO9sG2y3wiVM
SUMMARY:SY 101: Intro to Synthesis
DTSTAMP:20260323T153915Z
DTSTART:20260326T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Interested in learning more about synthesizers and how to devel
	op your own synthesized sounds In this informative 2-hour workshop\, our i
	nstructor will provide you with a detailed breakdown of the history of syn
	thesis\, Audio Path\, Modulation\, Basic Subtractive Patching\, and more!\
	n\n*The use of a laptop is required to participate in this class. You will
	 need to download VCV (free on laptops). Vera has a limited amount of lapt
	ops that we can provide on a first-come-first-serve basis to our members. 
	If you do have your own laptop\, we would appreciate if you used your own\
	, so we can provide laptops to those who may not have one. If you would li
	ke to request a laptop\, please email yewon.k@theveraproject.org. You will
	 also need to download a couple files for this workshop. These files will 
	be sent 24 hours before the class.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/Id4b6a4aa25a\n\
	nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/Id4b6a4aa25a
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:IIliUwseLOv80uTUuxWz1
SUMMARY:LS 101: Basics of Live Sound
DTSTAMP:20260323T153915Z
DTSTART:20260326T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Basics of Live Sound is a 2-hour introduction to live audio eng
	ineering and an orientation to Vera Project’s methods and equipment. Topic
	s covered include an introduction to microphones and mic placement\, signa
	l paths\, stands\, cables\, DI’s\, snake\, sub-snakes and etiquette for wo
	rking with bands. This class is designed for both the novices and experts 
	of all ages and will give an overview of signal flow and setting up small 
	PAs\, in addition to the basic requirements for being part of the Vera sou
	nd team at shows. Discover why the accommodating\, open minded “Vera Attit
	ude” of show production is appreciated worldwide!\n\nThis class is a prere
	quisite for advanced audio classes at Vera and Sound Runner shifts at Vera
	 Project show. Each Live Sound class unlocks new audio engineering volunte
	er shifts at Vera and eventually paid opportunities in and outside of the 
	venue. Become a volunteer at Vera to access other audio-related educationa
	l programs such as tours\, field trips\, and internships!\n\nhttps://link.
	dice.fm/rb7705edd6cb\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/rb7705edd6cb
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ZWgDlycHSYZ9tRs1YJinR
SUMMARY:SP 101: Intro to Vera's Screen Print Studio
DTSTAMP:20260323T153915Z
DTSTART:20260326T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 2-hour\, comprehensive hands-on class teaches you all the 
	basics of screen printing at Vera’s shop: From coating and burning a scree
	n\, to pulling your very first print! Get comfortable with Vera's shop lay
	out\, equipment\, and culture. Learn about techniques for creating screens
	\, terminology\, and more to create 1-color projects in the print shop. St
	udents will walk away with the basic skills for screen printing 1-color pa
	per prints\, and their own print of a special Vera design\, specific to th
	e 101 class.\n\nThis class is a prerequisite for other screenprint classes
	 at Vera and access to Open Sessions in Vera's studio. Open Sessions are m
	oderated by members of Vera's Screenprint Committee\, and can provide guid
	ance to participants on their projects. Open Sessions are scheduled for th
	ree times a month in 4 hour intervals. Participants must pay and register 
	for an Open Session in advance on Vera's website.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/
	Te6f7661a6ea\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/Te6f7661a6ea
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
